4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT EXPANDING OPPORTUNITIES FOR MULTIFAMILY FINANCING
5 UNDER THE COMMERCIAL PROPERTY-ASSESSED CAPITAL ENHANCEMENTS ACT; AMENDING
6 SECTION 90-4-1302, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 Section 1. Section 90-4-1302, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "90-4-1302. Definitions. As used in this part, unless the context requires otherwise, the following
12 definitions apply:
13 (1) "Authority" means the Montana facility finance authority created in 2-15-1815.
14 (2) "Commercial property-assessed capital enhancements program" or "program" means a
15 program established in accordance with this part.
16 (3) "District" means a district that is established under this part by a local government and that lies
17 within the local government's jurisdictional boundaries. A local government may create more than one district
18 under a program.
19 (4) "Energy conservation measure" means a permanent cost-effective energy improvement fixed
20 to real property, including new construction, and intended to decrease energy or water consumption and
21 demand, including a product, device, or interacting group of products or devices on the customer's side of the
22 meter that uses energy technology to generate electricity, provide thermal energy, or regulate temperature. The
23 term includes but is not limited to:
24 (a) insulation in walls, roofs, floors, foundations, or heating and cooling distribution systems;
25 (b) storm windows and doors, including multiglazed windows and doors, heat-absorbing or heat-
26 reflective glazed windows, coated window and door systems, additional glazing, reductions in glass area, and
27 other window and door system modifications that reduce energy consumption;
28 (c) automated energy control systems;
